    This class is a fixed non-editable portion of data of a BPlusIndexedSet defined by its lower and a upper bound and acts like a fixed range query. It is created by calling BPlusIndexedSet.subSet(Object, Object), BPlusIndexedSet.headSet(Object) or BPlusIndexedSet.tailSet(Object). Depending on set type a BPlusIndexedSetView contains the elements of the parent set which are greater or equal to the lower bound and (may be strictly) less than the upper bound.
    Please note: Because it is a fixed view not all methods of Java's SortedSet interface are supported. Although you can not edit the content of a view, it's content will be refreshed automatically if the source set changes. That means if a view v contains an item e and you remove e from the parent set, e will not be visible in v anymore.
